Suggestion : Test To Configure GUI SSH And IPMI Settings
I think this name is clear about test case.

Add test setup to fetch IPMI and SSH setting before starting the test case. And in the teardown restore the value back to the initial value.

[Setup]  Fetch IPMI And SSH setting
[Teardown]  Set SSH And IPMI State Via GUI  inital_ssh_setting  initial_ipmi_setting


Fetch IPMI And SSH setting
  ${initial_ssh_state}=  Get Text  ${xpath_bmc_ssh_toggle}
  Set Suite Variable  initial_ssh_state
  ${initial_ipmi_state}=  Get Text  ${xpath_ipmi_toggle}
  Set Suite Variable  initial_ssh_state

This keyword is for checking SSH and IPMI value both together. So we should mention the same in the keyword name. Also as we are not doing login as part of the keyword. Take it out of documentation. you can just keep it as.

Verify SSH And IPMI Policy State
    [Documentation]  Verify if the current SSH and IPMI setting matches with  
    ...  given values.

    Run Keyword If  '${ssh_state}' != '${new_ssh_state}'
    ...  Click Element  ${xpath_bmc_ssh_toggle}
    ...  ELSE IF  '${ssh_state}' == '${new_ssh_state}'
    ...  Log  SSH policy is already set to required state.

The main objective of this test case is, need to check the functionality of SSH/IPMI by clicking those elements at a time. If I use the above one then the clicking action will takes only once...So better to keep the code as it is.
